<HEADLINE> EC to Present Summit Report on Regional Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, December 11 (Xinhua) -- The European Commission, the
European Union (EU)'s executive body, said today that it would
present to the upcoming EU summit in Luxembourg a report on
regional cooperation in Europe.
</P>
<P>
The EU executive said in a press release issued here Thursday
that it supported the development of regional cooperation in
Europe as a means to promote stability, security and prosperity as
well as to further the process of European integration.
</P>
<P>
It proposed in the report that the EU's general approach to
regional cooperation should be based on existing political,
commercial and technical assistance instruments.
</P>
<P>
The Commission said that the importance of regional cooperation
would increase in the process of EU enlargement and its
development would promote the openness of the enlarged EU towards
its neighbors, helping to ensure that no new dividing lines were
drawn on the European continent.
</P>
<P>
The EU summit held in Dublin in December 1996 asked the EU
executive to report on the wide range of regional activities in
Europe at the upcoming summit which will take place in Luxembourg
Friday and Saturday.
</P>
<P>
It was learned that the report covered regional activities from
the Arctic to the Black Sea, where EU member states and their
neighbors in Europe participated. 
</P>
</TEXT>
