<HEADLINE> Arab League Denounces Israel's Ban on Palestinian </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, December 11 (Xinhua) -- The Arab League (AL) today
voiced deep resentment over the newly-adopted Israeli Knesset
(parliament) bill preventing the Palestinian National Authority
(PNA) from carrying out a census of Palestinian nationals in East
Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
"Such a decision is illegal and invalid as Arab Jerusalem has
been occupied by Israel since 1967," AL Spokesman Talaat Hammad
was quoted by Egypt's Middle East News Agency as saying.
</P>
<P>
He voiced the League's full support for the Palestinian people
and the PNA in all the measures, including the census, adopted on
the way towards the establishment of a Palestinian state with
Jerusalem as its capital.
</P>
<P>
After a long-time debate, the Israeli parliament at midnight
Wednesday adopted a bill blocking Palestinian census-takers from
operating in Jerusalem, arguing that the Palestinians'
unprecedented move would undermine Israel's claim to the disputed
city which it captured in 1967.
</P>
<P>
Israel also fears that a reliable census would give the
Palestinians an edge in future negotiations on the status of the
city.
</P>
<P>
The Palestinians have suggested that the census be conducted in
East Jerusalem which they claim as a future capital. An estimated
180,000 Palestinians live there.
</P>
<P>
The PNA said today it will carry out the census as planned, but
only through fax contacts in view of Israel's ban on such a move.
</P>
</TEXT>
