<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, December 11 (Xinhua) -- Etheopia's Ministry of
Health announced today that the second round polio vaccination
campaign will be launched as of tomorrow.
</P>
<P>
An official from the ministry said about 8.5 million children
are expected to be vaccinated in the campaign to be carried out
at the national level for the second time.
</P>
<P>
According to the official, 2,088 permanent and 25,297 mobile
stations have been established and one health professional and
two volunteers are giving services at each station.
</P>
<P>
the official said in spite of the success achieved in the first
round campaign which was launched last month in most parts of the
country, the vaccination activities have not been undertaken as
intended in Somali and afar regions due to the climate change
affected by the El Nino phenomenon.
</P>
<P>
Special attention will be given to the two regions, he
stressed.
</P>
<P>
According to the announcement, the second round campaign will
last three days. 
