<HEADLINE> Iraq Astonished at Jordan's Ouster of </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BAGHDAD, December 11 (Xinhua) -- Iraq said today that it is
astonished that Jordan has decided to expel Iraqi diplomats in
retaliation for its execution of four Jordanians.
</P>
<P>
At a press conference, a spokesman of Iraqi Foreign Ministry
said each country has its own jurisdiction, and that Jordan has
the knowledge through previous Iraqi memorandums that organized
smuggling from and to Iraq is a crime, of which the punishment is
execution according to Iraqi law.
</P>
<P>
He said that crimes of smuggling and economic sabotage are
great dangers to Iraq under the oil embargo imposed by the United
Nations in 1990 after its invasion of Kuwait.
</P>
<P>
Iraq executed four Jordanians Monday on charge of smuggling car
spare parts.
</P>
<P>
Jordan Wednesday issued a statement to condemn Iraq's execution
of four students, and demanded seven Iraqi diplomats leave the
kingdom within a week.
</P>
<P>
The Iraqi spokesman said that the four Jordanians had been
assisted by their accomplices both in Iraq and Jordan.
</P>
<P>
He identified the four executed as vehicle drivers, all above 30
years old, and members of an organized gang, rather than innocent
young students as Jordan said in its statement.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the spokesman said that the Iraqi people cherish
deep love for the Jordanian people and appreciate their genuine
Arab positions towards Iraq.
</P>
<P>
He expressed Iraq's hopes that Jordan will show understandings
to Iraq in dealing with the issue and not allow it to be exploited
to jeopardize the deep-rooted, honest and useful bilateral
relations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
