<HEADLINE> Russian Planes' Crash Claims Eight Lives </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, December 11 (Xinhua) -- Eight people were killed when a
helicopter and a plane collided on the runway in Naryan-Mar,
Arkhangelsk region, Thursday, the Interfax quoted the Russian
Ministry of Emergency Situations as reporting.
</P>
<P>
The crash occurred at 16:59 Moscow time (1359 GMT) as a Mi-8
helicopter with 16 people on board was on the runway just two
minutes before a landing An-12 plane hit it with its wing.
</P>
<P>
The helicopter at once caught fire and eight passengers were
killed, while three crew remaining unhurt.
</P>
<P>
The An-12 plane carried seven crew members and eight
passengers. Three out of the crew were seriously injured, two
others will have their feet amputated, and the remaining crew
members were safe and sound.
</P>
<P>
It was alleged that poor visibility may have been the cause of
the collision. 
</P>
