<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, December 11 (Xinhua) -- The United States on
Thursday accused Turkey of provocative flight over the northern
Aegean Sea, saying it could raise tensions between Turkey and
Greece, the two NATO member states.
</P>
<P>
"Military activity of this kind undermines confidence and
needlessly exacerbates tensions between our two NATO allies,"
State Department spokesman James Foley told reporters. "We call
on Turkey to stop such actions."
</P>
<P>
Foley was referring to Turkish air movements over the northern
Aegean near the Greek city of Thessalonki. The flights were
confirmed by NATO radar data.
</P>
