exercises and there were no penetration of Greek airspace by the
flights. And it said 10 Greek warplanes intercepted Turkish
aircraft in international airspace of the Aegean.
</P>
<P>
But Athens said its warplanes intercepted the Turkish jets
because they violated Greek airspace.
</P>
<P>
Foley said the United States was hopeful that a new command
structure for the Aegean will be able to prevent such
occurrences once it is in place.
</P>
<P>
The United States began an new initiative earlier this year
to try to resolve tensions between Turkey and Greece, as the
tensions have created instability in a key region ad have a
corrosive effect on NATO. 
