<HEADLINE> US Removes Mines on Border With Cuba </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, December 11 (Xinhua) -- The United States has
removed 11,000 of the 14,000 mines on the border with Cuba,
announced the Pentagon today.
</P>
<P>
"The removal is going carefully, but well," Pentagon spokesman
Kenneth Bacon said. There were at one point 14,000 mines on the
U.S. side of the border between the Guantanamo Bay Naval Station
and Cuba.
</P>
<P>
"I believe that 11,000 of those mines have been removed from
the U.S. side, leaving 3,000 more to remove," said the spokesman.
</P>
