<HEADLINE> Cambodian Plane Crashes on Training Flight, Killing Pilot </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, December 12 (Xinhua) -- A Cambodian air force
fighter plane crashed on Friday some 70 kilometers south of the
capital, killing the pilot, the only person on board.
</P>
<P>
The cause of the crash is under investigation.
</P>
<P>
The accident occurred in the southern province of Kandal at
14:40 local time, (0740 GMT) when the air force L39 ground attack
aircraft was on a training flight.
</P>
<P>
One of two such planes bought from Israel, it took off from the
Phnom Penh military air base and was flying 50 meters high before
it dived down, said General You Vireak, commander of the base.
</P>
</TEXT>
