<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 15:00 GMT, December 12 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK -- The Thai currency baht on Friday sank to a new low,
closing at 45.65 to the U.S. dollar, according to local TV
Channel 7.
</P>
<P>
The baht has lost 77 percent of its value against the dollar
since the baht was floated on July 2. (Thailand-Baht-Fall)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
LUXEMBOURG -- Turkey has turned down the invitation for its top
government official to dine with European Union (EU) leaders at
the weekend in Luxembourg.
</P>
<P>
Turkey's frustrated move, sources here said Friday, was due to
the EU's reluctance to include Ankara in its initial blueprint for
enlargement, somehow on political reasons. (Turkey-EU-Reject)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
LAGOS -- The Nigerian government has lifted a three-decade ban
on vessels to enter and depart its ports after 6:00 in the
evening, local media reported Friday.(Nigeria-ban lifted)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
LONDON -- A huge fire broke out at Terminal One at London's
Heathrow airport early Friday, causing extensive damage and
bringing chaos to the airport. (UK-Fire)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BANGKOK -- Thailand and Myanmar have agreed to demarcate their
common boundary by dividing it into 10 sectors, according to the
Nation newspaper Friday. (Thailand-Myanmar-Boundary)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- U.S. President Bill Clinton on Thursday urged
Americans to support the new international agreement on combating
global warming. (Clinton-International Agreement) 
</P>
