<HEADLINE> Police Launch Anti-Drug Operation Near Paris </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, December 12 (Xinhua) -- French police Friday launched an
anti-drug operation in an immigrant district at Gennevilliers
outside Paris, reported Agence France-Presse (AFP).
</P>
<P>
The agency said the operation was staged after some acts of
violence took place, including the sabotage of two vehicles and
telephone cabins, and after stones were thrown at police patrols
in the poor district northwest of Paris.
</P>
<P>
Nine people, most of them convicted drug dealers and abusers,
were questioned by police during the operation, said the report.
</P>
<P>
Some 20 young people threw jeers and exchanged fist blows with
police, while some local non-governmental organizations denounced
police for "muscular questionings" and "racist insults."
</P>
</TEXT>
