<DOCNO> XIE19971212.0077 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Canada's GDP Grows 1.0 Percent in Third Quarter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, December 12 (Xinhua) -- Canada's real gross domestic
product (GDP) grew 1.0 percent in the third quarter of this year,
Statistics Canada reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
This was 4.0 percent higher than the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
The strong growth came on the strength of domestic and foreign
demand, the federal statistics agency noted.
</P>
<P>
In the quarter, consumer spending and business investment in
plant and equipment continued to drive final domestic demand, which
was up 1.5 percent.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Canada's exports picked up by 2.4 percent, and imports
jumped by 4.6 percent.
</P>
<P>
This brought its balance of trade on goods and services to 3.8
billion dollars (2.7 billion U.S. dollars) in the third quarter,
down from 9.9 billion dollars in the second quarter. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
