<BODY>
<HEADLINE> France Begins Trial of Terrorist Carlos </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, December 12 (Xinhua) -- An Assize Court here began on
Friday the trial of Carlos, or Ilich Ramirez Sanchez, the alleged
murderer of some 20 people and a symbol of international terrorism
in 1970s and 80s.
</P>
<P>
Though the 48-year-old Venezuelan is charged with five attacks
in France, the trial is focused on the killing of two French
secret agents and their Lebanese informer on June 27, 1975, in his
dormitory in the Latin district of Paris.
</P>
<P>
If convicted, Carlos would face 30 years in prison.
</P>
<P>
Led by the Lebanese Michel Moukharbal, the agents with the
Direction of Territorial Security Raymond Dous and Jean Donatini,
as well as a police officer Jean Herranz, had come to arrest the
terrorist.
</P>
<P>
Carlos was accused of opening fire, killing three and seriously
wounding the police officer, before fled.
</P>
<P>
In 1984, however, he was abducted by French agents from Sudan
and has been imprisoned in the Fresne Prison of Paris ever since.
</P>
<P>
In June 1992, a French court sentenced, in his absence, life
imprisonment for the triple murder. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
