<HEADLINE> "Epoch Street" in Pudong New Area Gets Loan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, December 12 (Xinhua) -- The Industrial and Commercial
Bank of China (ICBC) today granted a 612 million yuan loan for the
construction of "Epoch Street" in the Pudong New Area of Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
"Epoch Street", formerly called "Central Road", the most
important road construction projects in Shanghai, will divide the
Pudong New Area into two parts from south to north. The street
will be completed and opened to traffic on December 31, 2000.
</P>
<P>
The street will link the center of the Pudong New Area and the
Lujiazui Finance and Trade Zone with the Hongqiao International
Airport.
</P>
<P>
According to local officials, the eight-lane road, which will
be 100 meters wide and 4.2 km long, will be built at a cost of
1.48 billion yuan. Many skyscrapers will be constructed at both
sides of the road, including the 88-storey Jinmao Building, the
Global Finance Building and the Shanghai Securities Building.
</P>
<P>
The road will also feature parks and green belts covering over
100,000 square meters.
</P>
<P>
The Pudong branch of ICBC has provided loans of over one
billion yuan for the construction of roads in Pudong over the past
years.  
</P>
</TEXT>
