<HEADLINE> Vietnam Sets Targets for 1998 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, December 12 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam's congress has approved
the government's socio-economic development plan featuring a 9
percent gross domestic product (GDP) growth in 1998.
</P>
<P>
The target, said media reports here, was contained in a
resolution submitted to the second session of the 10th National
Assembly, or congress, concluded here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
To substantiate the overall target for the coming year, the
government called for a 4.6-4.8 percent growth for agriculture and
a 13.5 percent growth for industrial production.
</P>
<P>
It also aimed to reach a 25-26 percent year-on-year increase in
total export earnings, keep the trade deficit and inflation below
20 percent and 7 percent respectively.
</P>
<P>
In the budget proposal, about 20 percent of GDP will go to the
state budget, and the budget deficit will be kept at 3.5-4 percent
of GDP in 1998, the resolution said.
</P>
<P>
Population growth is expected to be no more than 1.8 percent
next year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
