<HEADLINE> S.Leonean Military Junta Expresses Baffled Over </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FREETWON, December 12 (Xinhua)-- The Sierra Leonean military
government said Friday it is "baffled" over Thursday's
bombardment by a Nigerian Alfa jet on the village of Benduma in
the east in which 10 people were killed and another 18 seriously
injured.
</P>
<P>
According to Director of Defence Information John Milton, the
victims were all civilians including children.
</P>
<P>
" We don't know why the Nigerians picked on that target as the
village is inhabited by subsistence farmers who have nothing to
do with any political crisis," Milton said.
</P>
<P>
There has been no independent confirmation of the attack but a
Nigerian officer in the ECOMOG (west African peace keeping force)
base in Freetown said he is "surprised" over the charge, but as
far as we know no hostility has been ordered against Sierra Leone
during this period."
</P>
<P>
On Tuesday, Secretary General in the military government,Abdul
Sesay told a press conference that the ECOMOG was planning an
invasion on the Sierra Leonean capital with a 460 million dollar
support from a foreign country.
</P>
<P>
He said ECOMOG has already acquired 18 amphibious vehicles to
be used in the operation which has the approval of deposed
president Tejan Kabbah. Kabbah is now in Iran attending the
Islamic summit. 
</P>
</TEXT>
