Ecuador 6-4, 6-4 to set up a semifinal clash against South African
Johan Kriek.
</P>
<P>
Kriek, 39, looms as the danger man for tournament top seed and
eight-times grand slam singles champion Jimmy Connors, after
blowing Argentina's Jose-Luis Clerc away in less than an hour.
</P>
<P>
Kriek, the Australian Open winner in 1981 and 1982, won 6-1,
6-3.
</P>
