<HEADLINE> France Publishes Children's Weather Book </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, December 12 (Xinhua) -- A book explaining to children
the mysterious phenomena in climate and atmosphere, "Discover the
Meteorology," has been published by the French weather forecast
institute Meteo-France and Circonflexe publishing house.
</P>
<P>
The author, Didier Renaut, who is an engineer of Meteo-France,
uses an alternative way to explain the mechanisms of climate,
introduces a series of weather observation tools, such as
satellites, observation stations, electronic models,
radio-surveyors, as well as the work of meteorologists.
</P>
<P>
The book, full of illustrations and only using a limited
storage of scientific words and terms, explains how scientists
observe the atmosphere, predict the weather in the coming days,
and study the evolution of the climate of the Earth. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
