<HEADLINE> Chinese Neurosurgery Committee Established in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, December 12 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese Neurosurgery
Committee was established today in Shanghai, China's largest
Manufacturing city.
</P>
<P>
The birth of the Committee will promote the neurological
research in the country.
</P>
<P>
The committee will serve as a center for training doctors
specialized in neurosurgery and promoting international academic
exchanges, according to an expert member of the committee.
</P>
<P>
Experts note that China ranks first in the world with more than
one million neurosurgery patients annually.
</P>
<P>
Therefore, it was essential to establish a national
organization to strengthen research related to neurosurgery,
according to experts.
</P>
<P>
China has over 6,000 neurosurgery specialists. The efforts in
neurological research in the past four decades have ensured that
the nation has maintained international levels in the sector.
