<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Military Leader Meets Commander of US Pacific Command </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 12 (Xinhua) -- Gen. Zhang Wannian,
vice-chairman of China's Central Military Commission, met today
with Admiral Joseph Prueher, commander-in-chief of the US Pacific
Command.
</P>
<P>
Zhang noted that the Sino-US relations have grown in recent
years, despite various twists and turns in the process.
</P>
<P>
The Sino-US cooperation has been expanded and has great
potentials, according to Zhang.
</P>
<P>
He said that President Jiang Zemin's successful state visit to
the United States has not only laid a solid foundation for the two
nations to forge a constructive strategic partnership oriented to
the 21st century, but also created new opportunities for the
further development of bilateral military ties.
</P>
<P>
Zhang pointed out that properly handling the subtle Taiwan
issue in accordance with the principles of the three Sino-US joint
communiques will promote the further development of bilateral
relations.
</P>
<P>
The two sides should practice mutual respect and conduct dialog
on an equal footing, said Zhang.
</P>
<P>
"China attaches great importance to the relation between the
Chinese and US armies and is fully prepared to boost its
development," he said.
</P>
<P>
"We sincerely hope that military leaders of the two armies will
maintain regular exchanges of visit and dialog so as to deepen
mutual understanding.
</P>
<P>
"Relations between the two armed forces will have a bright
future so long as the two sides respect each other and engage in
sincere cooperation."
</P>
<P>
He expressed appreciation of Prueher's efforts for the
development of the relations between the two nations and their
armed forces.
</P>
<P>
He said Prueher's visit will help promote the further
development of bilateral military ties.
</P>
<P>
Prueher said Jiang Zemin's recent visit to the US has opened
broad prospects for the Sino-US relations in the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
He said the relationship between the two armed forces is an
extremely important aspect of bilateral relations, and expressed
the hope that the two armed forces will expand contacts and mutual
understanding in order to promote the constructive and balanced
development of bilateral military ties.
</P>
<P>
He expressed great appreciation of China's achievements in
various fields.
</P>
<P>
With regard to the Taiwan issue, Prueher said the US side fully
understands that it is directly related to China's sovereignty. He
stressed that the US should handle the issue in a careful and
responsible manner.
</P>
<P>
Kui Fulin, deputy chief of General Staff of the Chinese
People's Liberation Army, Luo Bin, director of the Foreign Affairs
Bureau of the National Defense Ministry, and US Ambassador to
China James Sasser attended the meeting. 
</P>
</TEXT>
