<HEADLINE> DPR Korea Fights into Final at Asian Women's Soccer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, December 12 (Xinhua) -- A three-minute blankpoint
shot fired DPR Korea past Japan to the final of the 11th Asian
Women's Soccer Championships here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The narrow victory also sent the DPR Koreans through to Women's
World Cup Soccer Championship, which is to be held in the United
States in 1999, since the top three teams of the tournament will
be qualified.
</P>
<P>
The scoreline was reading 1-0 three minutes into the game when
the Korean striker Kim Kun Sil struck from close range on a
pinpoint cross from playmaker Ri Un Sim, and stood unchanged ever
since.
</P>
<P>
Head coach of DPR Korea, Myong Tong Chan, said after the match
that he had not expected this victory over Japan, which he thought
was more skillful and experienced. 
