<HEADLINE> Chinese Premier Meets Uzbekistan Foreign Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 12 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Li Peng said
here today that Chinese government values its friendly and
cooperative ties with Uzbekistan, a close neighbor and an
important cooperative partner of China in central Asia.
</P>
<P>
He made the remarks during a meeting with visiting Uzbekistan
Foreign Minister Kamilov Abdulaziz Hafizovich.
</P>
<P>
Sino-Uzbekistan relations have witnessed smooth development
since the two countries forged diplomatic ties six years ago, Li
said, adding that the frequent contacts between the leaders of the
two countries have greatly advanced bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
The premier went on to say that a good momentum of development
has been maintained in Sino-Uzbekistan economic and trade ties,
with a steady growth of bilateral trade volume and an expansion of
cooperation in other fields. "China is satisfied with the
development of Sino-Uzbekistan relations," he said.
</P>
<P>
Li voiced the hope that the enterprises of the two countries
would continue to increase mutual exchange and cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Central Asia is an important region with a broad development
prospect, Li said, emphasizing that China is ready to develop a
long-term and stable relationship of cooperation with the nations
in this region.
</P>
<P>
Kamilov said that the Uzbekistan government attaches major
importance to its relations with China. The high-level exchange of
visits between the two countries plays an irreplaceable role in
promoting bilateral ties, he said.
</P>
<P>
He told Li that Uzbekistan hopes to expand its cooperation with
China in such areas as communications and transportation.
</P>
<P>
The foreign minister reaffirmed that Uzbekistan would persist
in the "one China" position. 
</P>
</TEXT>
