<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Slalom Cancelled by Snow in Val-D'Isere </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, December 12 (Xinhua) -- A women's Alpine skiing World
Cup giant slalom scheduled on Friday was forced to cancel because
of heavy snow.
</P>
<P>
On Thursday dense fog caused the cancellation of the women's
Super-G race.
</P>
<P>
A men's downhill and a men's giant slalom due on Saturday
and Sunday were expected to go ahead.
</P>
<P>
Organisers were also hoping to stage a men's downhill
training session on Friday afternoon after triggering off an
avalanche to clear excess snow off the piste.
</P>
<P>
It was not the first time the Savoie resort was affected by bad
weather conditions. In 1991, a year before the Albertville
Olympics, four races had to be called off because of snowfalls.
</P>
</TEXT>
