<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Soeharto Cancels Plan to Attend ASEAN Informal Summit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, December 12 (Xinhua) -- Indonesian President Soeharto,
on the advice of his doctors, has canceled his plan to attend next
week's informal ASEAN summit in Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia, a senior
official said here today.
</P>
<P>
The president has instructed Foreign Minister Ali Alatas to
represent him at the informal summit, to be held on December 15
and 16, Minister/State Secretary Moerdiono said.
</P>
<P>
Soeharto also gave up his plan to visit the grave of his late
wife, Tien Soeharto, in Solo, East Java Province, on Saturday
since his doctors advised him not to take a long trip, Moerdiono
said.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, the president had also decided not to make a trip to
Tehran, Iran, to attend the summit meeting of the Organization of
the Islamic Conference from December 9 to 11. Doctors had advised
him to take a full 10-day rest.
</P>
<P>
The president needs to further restore his health despite the
fact that he has fully recovered from his overseas trip from
November 18 to 29 which took him to Namibia, South Africa, Canada
and Saudi Arabia, said Moerdiono, who together with Alatas visited
the presidential residence.
</P>
<P>
"If the president makes another long trip, it could take a
longer time for him to restore his health," he added.
</P>
<P>
In the meantime, Alatas said that during the informal ASEAN
summit, the nine members of the Association of Southeast Asian
Nations (ASEAN) will meet with three of their dialogue partners --
China, Japan and South Korea.
</P>
<P>
Alatas said he will deliver a message from Soeharto on the
cancellation of his participation in the informal summit to
Malaysian Prime Minister Mahathir Mohammad.
</P>
<P>
On Wednesday, Moerdiono said Soeharto had decided to attend the
ASEAN meeting amid rumors that the president was seriously ill.
</P>
<P>
The rumors had pushed the value of the Indonesian rupiah to a
record low of 4,600 against the U.S. dollar, about 90 percent
lower than at the beginning of this year. The currency
strengthened Thursday after the announcement of Soeharto's
decision to attend the summit.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that the summit will discuss the monetary
crisis in Southeast Asia and how to face the 21st century in East
Asia and Southeast Asia.
</P>
<P>
ASEAN groups Brunei, Indonesia, Malaysia, Myanmar, Laos, the
Philippines, Singapore, Thailand and Vietnam.  
</P>
</TEXT>
