<HEADLINE> State Council Approves Regulations on Slaughtering Pigs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 12 (Xinhua) -- China will issue regulations
to restor order in pig-slaughtering business.
</P>
<P>
The Regulations on the Management of Slaughtering Pigs was
deliberated and approved here today at the 64th executive meeting
of the State Council, which was presided over by Premier Li Peng.
</P>
<P>
The purpose of the regulations is to ensure the quality of pig
meat and protect people's health, according to the meeting.
</P>
<P>
Pork is perhaps the most important daily non-staple food for
the Chinese. Slaughtering pigs at places without necessary
sanitary conditions has become a serious problem in some provinces
and cities. 
</P>
</TEXT>
