<HEADLINE> Vice-Premier Meets Fiji Foreign Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 12 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-Premier Zou
Jiahua met with Fiji Minister of Foreign Affairs and Trade
Berenado Wunibobo at the Diaoyutai State Guesthouse here today.
</P>
<P>
Zou said that both China and Fiji are developing countries in
the Asia-Pacific region. Both countries are facing the common task
of developing their economies and improving their peoples' living
standards.
</P>
<P>
He said that further increasing friendly cooperative relations
between the two countries is in the fundamental interests of the
two sides. He noted that China always holds that all countries,
big or small, rich or poor and strong or weak, are equal members
of the international community.
</P>
<P>
He said that China values its relations with South Pacific
countries, including Fiji. He said that China supports South
Pacific island nations in their efforts to safeguard their
sovereignty and territorial integrity, and to expand their
economies and to promote regional cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Zou stressed that the Chinese side will continue to push
forward Sino-Fijian economic and trade cooperation in line with
the principle of equality, mutual benefit, long-term cooperation
and common development.
</P>
<P>
Wunibobo said that Fiji places great emphasis on developing
relations with China. He said that the two countries have had
mutually beneficial cooperation in cultural, educational, health
and military area. He said that Fiji hopes to further expand the
scale and area of cooperation with China. 
</P>
