<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tanker Explosion Kills 7 in Nigeria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, December 12 (Xinhua) -- At least seven people were
feared to have been roasted to death when fire caused by the
explosion of a tanker engulfed no fewer than eight houses
Thursday night in the capital city of Ogun State, western
Nigeria.
</P>
<P>
Also burnt beyond redemption were two trailer tankers, one
tipper lorry and a taxi cab, while an estimated 15 persons were
severely injured, the Daily Champion reported today.
</P>
<P>
The paper quoted eye-witnesses as saying that the inferno
started at about 7:30 Thursday evening when a petrol tanker
ascending a sloppy hill suddenly lost gravity and its tank tipped
against a nearby house by the road.
</P>
<P>
A resultant explosion ignited fire sparks which, one after
another, almost completely razed down no fewer than eight houses,
including two-story buildings.
</P>
<P>
As incident occurred on the hill top, the sight of the flames
was visibly growing in almost every part of Abeokuta, an ancient
city about 100 km to the Nigeria-Benin border.
</P>
<P>
The fire was still raging as of 10:00 Thursday night and the
efforts of the state fire service firemen, who arrived at the
scene early enough with their engines, seemed to make little
success, the report said.
</P>
<P>
Official accounts of casualties and victims are yet to be
known. 
</P>
</TEXT>
