<HEADLINE> Nigeria Ports Lift Night Navigation Ban </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, December 20 (Xinhua) -- The Nigerian government has
lifted a three-decade ban on vessels to enter and depart its
ports after 6:00 in the evening, local media reported today.
</P>
<P>
Nicholas Akani, manager of the tin can island port in Lagos
confirmed this to the press here Thursday, adding that the
resumption of night sail would commence as soon as appropriate
machinery was put into place.
</P>
<P>
The ban on night navigation at Nigerian ports was imposed
during the civil war in late 1960s. It has been considered as a
major weakness on the Nigerian side in its bid to become the
World Bank designated west African transit center. 
</P>
</TEXT>
