<HEADLINE> Chinese Vice-Premier Meets British Businessman </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 12 (Xinhua) -- Vice-Premier Wu Bangguo,
meeting today with Patrick Paul, chairman of the British Chamber
of Commerce in Hong Kong, said that the Chinese government is
confident of the future of Hong Kong, despite the current
financial turmoil in parts of Asia.
</P>
<P>
He pointed to the well-shaped financial supervision system and
favorable economic basis in the territory, adding that Hong Kong's
stability benefits from the sustained, rapid and sound economic
development in China's inland areas.
</P>
<P>
He also described as bridge the role of the chamber of commerce
in promoting economic and trade exchanges between Hong Kong and
China's inland areas and between Britain and China.
</P>
<P>
Wu briefed Paul on China's reform and opening-up, especially
state-owned enterprise reform and financial reform.
</P>
<P>
Paul said that his chamber of commerce is pleased to see the
current situation in the region since Hong Kong's return five
months ago. The "one country, two systems" formula is operating
well there, he added.
</P>
<P>
The British Chamber of Commerce in Hong Kong has a good
relationship of cooperation with the China Council for the
Promoting of International Trade, he said, and that his
organization is fully prepared to boost economic and trade
cooperation between the two countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
