<HEADLINE> Hu Jintao Meets With Mongolian NDP Leader </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 12 (Xinhua) -- Hu Jintao, member of the
Standing Committee of the Chinese Communist Party (CPC) Central
Committee's Political Bureau, said here today that
the Chinese and Mongolian peoples have a tradition of friendly
feelings towards each other.
</P>
<P>
Hu made the remarks while meeting with a Mongolian National
Democratic Party delegation led by its vice-president Bat-uul,
</P>
<P>
The CPC and the Chinese government have always placed great
importance on the good-neighborly relations with Mongolia, and
have respected the social system and the road of development
chosen by the Mongolian people in accordance with their own
circumstances, he said.
</P>
<P>
Hu said he is glad that the Mongolian NDP has sent a delegation
here to officially establish friendly relations with the CPC. "We
are ready to set up and develop friendly relations with the
Mongolian party in line with the four principles of acting
independently, full equality, mutual respect and non-interference
in each other's internal affairs and further promote the
good-neighborly Sino-Mongolia ties in a comprehensive, stable and
healthy way," he said.
</P>
<P>
Bat-uul said that his party is pleased to see that bilateral
co-operation in the economic, trade, scientific, and cultural
sectors has continued to increase in recent years, and that
Mongolia appreciates China's achievements in the reforms and
opening-up to the outside world.
</P>
<P>
He said that his party is willing to develop friendly
co-operative ties with the CPC to further enhance relations between
the two nations.
</P>
<P>
The Mongolian delegation arrived in China on December 8. They
are here as guest of the CPC. On December 9, they held talks with
Dai Bingguo, director of the International Department of the CPC
Central Committee.
</P>
<P>
The delegation will also visit Hefei and Shanghai cities.
</P>
