<HEADLINE> Macao Bank Enters World Top 1,000 List </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, December 12 (Xinhua) -- Tai Fung Bank, a leading local
bank, has entered the world top 1,000 list to become the
only locally-funded bank in Macao for the entry.
</P>
<P>
Data released by the bank, which moved into its new
headquarters building today, said the monthly magazine "The
Banker" gave the bank 986th place in terms of strength.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the Macao-based bank ranked 956th in terms of
dimensions, 261st in terms of consolidation, 134th in terms of
capital profit returns and 117th in terms of property profit
returns.
</P>
<P>
First established in 1941 as a money exchange shop by the then
well-known local businessman Ho In and others, Tai Fung Bank was
registered as the first local-capital bank in 1972.
</P>
<P>
In 1984, the Bank of China joined in, holding half of the
bank's shares. The registered capital was raised to 160 million
patacas (about 20 million U.S. dollars at the 1984 exchange rate).
</P>
<P>
After the capital injection from the Bank of China, Tai Fung Bank
has grown into the largest local-capital bank in Macao, with its
total assets reaching 16.05 billion patacas (about 2.03 billion
dollars), 10 times those in 1984.
</P>
<P>
The bank has established commission relationship with more
than 300 banks around the world and also has a representative
office in Guangzhou, capital of South China's Guangdong Province.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
