<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka Announces New Scholarship Scheme </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, December 12 (Xinhua) -- The Sri Lankan government
today announced the establishment of a new scholarship scheme to
make higher education in Sri Lanka and overseas available to
selected candidates from public servants and their children.
</P>
<P>
Under the new scheme, public servants and their children can
apply for higher education in Sri Lankan or overseas universities,
the Presidential Secretariat said this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
A special selection panel will assess the applicants'
performance and choose candidates for the scholarships, which will
be funded by the President Fund.
</P>
<P>
The move aims to build an efficient public service with high
integrity and honesty, according to the secretariat.
</P>
<P>
There are about 1 million people working in government bodies,
state-owned companies, the military and police forces.
</P>
<P>
The new package will enable about 140 people annually,
including 30 children of public sector employees and 20 youths who
may not be children of public servants, to have access to higher
education either in Sri Lanka or in other countries.
</P>
<P>
Before the new scheme was announced, there were only three to
five scholarships awarded annually from the President Fund.
</P>
</TEXT>
