<HEADLINE> Fire Occurs at London Airport Building </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, December 12 (Xinhua) -- A huge fire broke out at
Terminal One at London's Heathrow airport early Friday, causing
extensive damage and bringing chaos to the airport.
</P>
<P>
The airport was closed for a time after the blaze started in
the roof void of a burger bar at around 0440 GMT.
</P>
<P>
The fire was brought under control after being tackled by 100
firefighters, the airport said Friday morning in a statement.
</P>
<P>
"The fire is now fully under control and the fire service are
currently assessing the damage," the statement said.
</P>
<P>
There were no reports of injuries, but officials said damage
appeared to be considerable.
</P>
<P>
The fire has affected flights throughout Britain. Until at
least 1500 GMT, all flights at Terminal One, which mainly handles
domestic flights, had been cancelled, British Airways Plc said.
</P>
<P>
Efforts were being made around 0730 GMT to reopen the access
road, but passengers were advised to check before leaving for the
airport. 
</P>
