<HEADLINE> Southwest China Province Cracks Down on Drug Crimes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUIYANG, December 12 (Xinhua) -- Southwest China's Guizhou
Province cracked a total of 1,649 drug-related cases from
September to November this year.
</P>
<P>
From the three month period, the Guizhou provincial police
arrested 2,203 people involved in drug-trafficking and confiscated
50 kilograms of heroin and 12.4 kilograms of opium, according to
a local police spokesman.
</P>
<P>
The police in Guizhou and Guangdong provinces jointly
detected a big drug-trafficking ring, arresting 15 suspected
criminals, seizing 33.72 kilograms of heroin and confiscating
100,000 yuan.
</P>
<P>
This was the biggest drug trafficking case in five years,
according to the spokesman.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman also revealed that the Guizhou provincial police
cracked a big "ice drug" case earlier this month, confiscating 800
grailograms of heroin and 12.4 kilograms of opium.
</P>
<P>
About 3,600 addicts have been put into rehabilitation centers
to help them kick their drug habits.
</P>
<P>
Guizhou Province is located on an international drug
trafficking route through Yunnan Province, which is adjacent to
Southeast Asia's Golden Triangle.  
</P>
</TEXT>
