<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU Summit Opens in Luxembourg </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUXEMBOURG, December 12 (Xinhua) -- European Union (EU) leaders
gathered in Luxembourg today for a two-day summit on EU's eastward
expansion and other pressing issues.
</P>
<P>
Heads of state and government of the 15 EU member countries and
Jacques Santer, president of the European Commission (EC), are
also expected to discuss EU's institutional reform and
agricultural policy among other things.
</P>
<P>
The 15 members need to find a consensus on whether to start
entry talks with all the 11 EU applicants or accept the
five-plus-one configuration recommended by the EC, the EU's
executive body, in July.
</P>
<P>
The five-plus-one configuration is made up by Poland, Hungary,
the Czech Republic, Estonia, Slovenia and Cyprus, candidates the
EU considers to be advanced in political and economic terms. The
other five "pre-ins" are Bulgaria, Romania, Latvia, Lithuania and
Slovakia.
</P>
<P>
The EU leaders are expected to discuss if they need to set up a
European Conference to group the 11 candidates and Turkey, which
is also applying for EU membership.
</P>
<P>
Foreign ministers failed in their last attempt Monday in
Brussels to find a compromise on the issue. The EC proposed to
start talks first with five-plus-one while Sweden and Denmark
suggested that negotiations be started with all the 11
candidates. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
