<HEADLINE> More Foreign Investment For Eastern Chinese Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, December 12 (Xinhua) -- Development zones in east
China's Shandong Province brought in 459 million US dollars worth
of foreign investment in the January-September period, 18.9
percent more than for the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
The Provincial Commission of Foreign Trade and Economic
Relations said that during the same period, the zones produced
28.2 billion yuan worth of industrial goods and exported 106
million US dollars worth of goods, 55.4 percent and 44.9 percent
more than for the corresponding period last year.
</P>
<P>
The commission attributes the foreign investment increase to
better infrastructure and services. The zones have approved 2,666
foreign investment projects, worth 5.75 billion US dollars. So far
2.45 billion US dollars has been actually invested.
</P>
<P>
Mitsubishi, Siemens, and Samsung are among the major foreign
companies in Shandong.  
</P>
</TEXT>
