<HEADLINE> China Breaks Three More Records at Weightlifting Worlds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHIANG MAI, THAILAND, December 12 (Xinhua) -- China's Hua Ju
broke three world records and grabbed two titles in the women's
76kg class at the World Weightlifting Championships here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Hua, who won the overall title, set the snatch record of 107.5
kgs and the jerk mark of 140.5kgs for the overall total of 247.5
kg.
</P>
<P>
But Aysel Ozgur of Turkey beat Hua's snatch record with a lift
of 110 kgs later.
</P>
<P>
Ozgur, who ranked second overall, stopped Hua from wrapping up
the three golds from the class.
</P>
<P>
The previous 76kg class records were all held by the Chinese
women. Gao Xiaoyan held the snatch mark of 106.5 kgs, Zhang
Guimei had the jerk record of 140.0 kgs as well as the overall
with 235 kgs. 
</P>
