<DOCNO> XIE19971212.0205 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Imports, Exports of Aquatic Products Rise </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 12 (Xinhua) -- China's import and export of
aquatic products totalled 2.09 million tons at a value of 3.5
billion U.S. dollars in the first 10 months of this year.
</P>
<P>
They represent 18-percent and 32-percent increases,
respectively, compared with the same period last year, Zhuo
Youzhan, director of the Fishery Bureau under the Ministry of
Agriculture, said here today.
</P>
<P>
The exports covered more than 70 countries and regions, mainly
to Japan, the Republic of Korea, the United States and Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
In the first 10 months, China produced 23.93 million tons of
aquatic products, 16 percent up from last year. Sea fishery rose
15 percent at 14.65 million tons. Freshwater products soared 17
percent at 9.28 million tons.
</P>
<P>
Zhuo predicted that China's annual output of aquatic products
would increase by nine percent this year.
</P>
<P>
Since the beginning of this year, all fishing areas have
readjusted the product mix and succeeded in expanding the water
areas for cultivation.
</P>
<P>
This year, farmers raised fish on 1.6 million hectares of paddy
fields, 15 percent more than last year.
</P>
<P>
Zhuo called for fishing areas to deepen reforms, spread the use
of improved varieties and raise per unit output and
efficiency. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
