<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Survey: Majority of Shanghai Couples Content with Marriage </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 12 (Xinhua) -- A Lastest survey in Shanghai
shows that two-thirds of 800 married couples surveyed are content
with their marriages, while nearly one-third of them thought it
just so-so.
</P>
<P>
The survey found that 94.5 percent of men and 94.4 percent of
women chose their own partners. Those who sought parental opinions
did so voluntarily.
</P>
<P>
The couples, who met each other by chance accounted for 45.6
percent of the total, while the rest used matchmakers, according
to today's Wenhui Daily.
</P>
<P>
Most of these surveyed still pursue the criteria they set for
choosing a partner before getting married. Their criteria included
health, age, character and habits, the paper said.
</P>
<P>
Only a few said they would pick job titles and income as
criteria rather than family background and political status if
they chose again.
</P>
<P>
Though only 36.8 percent of males and 29 percent of females say
they married for love, about 90 percent of the males and 83
percent of the females said they were quite satisfied with their
partners after marriage. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
