<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading Kenyan Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, December 12 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news
items in leading Kenyan newspapers today.
</P>
<P>
Kenya Times
</P>
<P>
-- Four political parties have been disqualified from the
December 29 General Election for failing to subscribe to the
Electoral Code of Conduct.
</P>
<P>
-- Kenyans will today mark the 34th anniversary of Jamburi Day
with the climax of the celebrations being marked by President
Daniel arap Moi's keynote address to the nation at the Nyayo
National stadium.
</P>
<P>
Daily Nation
</P>
<P>
-- U.S. Secretary of State Madeleine Albright yesterday
pledged to give Rwanda the full moral and financial support of
the United States, saying the little country's future was
critical to the region.
</P>
<P>
-- Separatists who have declared independence on two Comoran
islands showed no willingness to negotiate with the Grande Comore
government yesterday as they went into closed-door reconciliation
talks in Addis Ababa.
</P>
<P>
East African Standard
</P>
<P>
-- Campaign for the December 29 General Election officially
kicked off yesterday after the Electoral Commission cleared 715
candidates to vie for 198 parliamentary seats countrywide.
</P>
</TEXT>
