<HEADLINE> Pharmacies Authorized to Put up Green Cross for Quality </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 12 (Xinhua) -- Some 234 pharmacies in Beijing
have become the first to put up a green cross as a mark of quality
after receiving certificates for standardized services.
</P>
<P>
Another 19 pharmacies, which did not pass the appraisal of the
Beijing Municipal Pharmaceutical Bureau, have been temporarily
closed, according to today's "Beijing Daily."
</P>
<P>
About 94 percent of the 478 pharmacies in Beijing passed the
appraisal conducted by the bureau in accordance with the Service
Regulations for Pharmacies, which was issued in July of this year,
the paper said.
</P>
<P>
Half of the approved pharmacies received certificates on Monday
and were authorized to use the green cross.
</P>
<P>
The bureau will revoke the licenses of the 19 pharmacies which
failed the appraisal if they do not pass a second examination.
</P>
</TEXT>
