<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tianjin Bonded Zone Exerting Strong Influence on Foreign Trade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, December 12 (Xinhua) -- The Bonded Zone of Tianjin,
the leading industrial center in north China, has become an
import-export distribution center with a sphere of influence
covering Beijing, Tianjin, the Bohai Sea Rim and the central and
western regions.
</P>
<P>
Between January and November, goods held at the bonded zone's
customs office were valued at 2.5 billion U.S. dollars, a 64
percent rise over the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
Officials of the bonded zone attributed the growth to improved
services.
</P>
<P>
Simplified procedures have helped lower enterprises' foreign
trade costs. The area's efficiency has improved because 95 percent
of the businesses engaged in foreign trade and processing have
been connected with the customs office's computer network.
</P>
<P>
The bonded zone also has emphasized exports. It is now the only
bonded zone in northern and northwestern China.
</P>
<P>
The zone offers favorable policies to imports and exports from
the central and western regions, which are rich in natural
resources but lack funding and are dependent on the port for their
foreign trade. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
