<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New Domestic Air Routes Between Major Tourist Cities Planned </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 12 (Xinhua) -- Two air routes linking the
tourist city of Datong with Beijing and with Guangzhou are
scheduled to begin service December 30.
</P>
<P>
Endorsed by the Civil Aviation Administration of China, China
Xinhua Airlines will fly two trips every Tuesday and Saturday
linking Datong with Beijing and Guangzhou.
</P>
<P>
Located in the northern part of Shanxi Province in north China,
Datong boasts the world-renowned Yungang Grottoes, the Huayan
Monastery and Nine-dragon Screen among its more than 300
historical sites and scenic spots.
</P>
<P>
Near the city is a Buddhist temple suspended above cliffs of
the Hengshan Mountain and the Yingxian Wooden Pagoda. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
