<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> IBF To Launch SuperSeries In 1999 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, December 12 (Xinhua) -- The International Badminton
Federation (IBF) announced Thursday that it would upgrade key
World Grand Prix Open tournaments to the new elite badminton
"SuperSeries" events slated in 1999.
</P>
<P>
The new badminton tournament is aimed at raising the profile of
the world's fastest racket sport.
</P>
<P>
Ten existing organisers have filed an application for their
events to be elevated to SuperSeries status, although a maximum of
seven will be selected by IBF.
</P>
<P>
The tournaments will have a "distinctive presentational
approach", though the negotiation for SuperSeries status
requirements is still under way.
</P>
<P>
At the elite events, a minimum of 250,000 U.S. dollars in prize
money will be awarded with world ranking points increased. 
</P>
</TEXT>
