<HEADLINE> Argentina Welcomes Chinese Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, December 11 (Xinhua) -- Argentine President Carllos
Saul Menem said on Thursday that the Argentine government welcomes
investments from Chinese entrepreneurs in Argentina. He also
called for enterprises of the two countries to further develop
their cooperation.
</P>
<P>
President Menem made the above comment while meeting the
leaders of Dalian Huafeng Enterprise, one of the largest Chinese
private companies. During the meeting, President Menem said that
it is a good step for the Huafeng group to invest in Argentina and
sign contracts with Argentine companies, which will accelerate
reciprocal investment between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
According to a contract signed on Wednesday in the presidential
residence, Dalian Huafeng Enterprise of China will co-invest with
four other companies of Germany, Argentina, Italy and the United
States to build a beef processing plant. The total investment for
the first phase will amount to 40 million U.S. dollars and Dalian
Huafeng group will receive a 10 percent share of the venture.
</P>
<P>
Dalian Huafeng group, a business entity with its own port,
hotel, chain stores and gulf course, is the first Chinese private
company to invest in Argentina. 
</P>
</TEXT>
