<DOCNO> XIE19971212.0243 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Italian Chamber Approves Return of House of Savoy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, December 11 (Xinhua) -- The Italian lower house approved
by a wide margin Thursday a bill to allow the male descendants of
the House of Savoy to return to Italy. The bill must now go before
the Senate.
</P>
<P>
The house vote, by secret ballot, was 276-204. The ruling
center-left Olive Tree coalition was not united behind the return
of the Savoys. Those declaring themselves against the bill were
the Communist Refoundation, the Republicans and the United
Communists. The center-right Freedom Front was in favor of the
bill.
</P>
<P>
The government bill has been significantly modified by the
Constitutional Affairs Committee. Even after the Senate votes on
it, at least another three months will go by before any
constitutional changes can be made on the basis of deliberations
in the two houses.
</P>
<P>
Male offspring of the House of Savoy are banned from Italy, but
on the occasion of the 50th anniversary of the Italian Republic
last year, President Oscar Luigi Scalfaro indicated it was time to
review the ban. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
