<HEADLINE> Indian Govt Reduces Prices of Commonly-Used Drugs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, December 12 (Xinhua)-- The Indian government has
decided to reduce the prices of 72 medical formulations in a bid
to curb over-charging and make available commonly-used medicines
at affordable rates, official sources said today.
</P>
<P>
The reduction in prices of commonly-used medicines including
those administered for fever, cough, headache, pain relief and
skin diseases, and vitamins and oral and injectable antibiotics
have been slashed by anything between 0.17 and 16 percent.
</P>
<P>
A decision to this effect was taken at a meeting of the
National Pharmaceutical Pricing Authority (NPPA) here on Thursday.
</P>
