<HEADLINE> Clinton Asks Americans to Support Global Warming Treaty </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, December 11 (Xinhua) -- U.S. President Bill Clinton
on Thursday urged Americans to support the new international agreement
on combating global warming.
</P>
<P>
Clinton made the call at a Coast Guard station in Miami in his
travel for political fund raising.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. president recalled, "Every time we've tried to improve
the American environment in the last 25 or 30 years, somebody has
predicted that it would wreck the economy."
</P>
<P>
Countering his opponents, Clinton said, the air and water are
cleaner, the food supply is safer and there are fewer toxic waste
sites than five years ago.
</P>
<P>
The president's appeal came just hours after delegates from 150
nations, meeting in Japan, approved a pact to control
heat-trapping greenhouse gases.
</P>
<P>
Clinton praised the accord as environmentally strong and
economically sound. But Republican critics in Congress denounced
it and predicted it would never be ratified by the Senate.
</P>
</TEXT>
