<HEADLINE> Panama Sends Home Colombian Criminals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PANAMA CITY, December 11 (Xinhua) -- Forty-three Colombian
criminals involved in drug-trafficking were sent home by the
Panamanian government on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The criminals flew out in an aircraft provided by the Colombian
air force, The repatriation was carried out under a 1994 agreement
between the two governments which provides for criminal offenders
to be sent to their homelands to continue their prison terms after
serving half their terms.
</P>
<P>
Colombian consular officials praised the Panamanian side for its
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
There are l39 Colombian drug traffickers who have been
sentenced in Panama, and 284 other suspected or awaiting
sentencing traffickers.
</P>
<P>
Official sources said there were two Panama criminals serving
prison terms in Colombia in keeping with the repatriation
conditions. 
</P>
