<HEADLINE> Sri Lankan Rebels Target 17 Locations in Colombo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, December 12 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lankan security forces
have set up more checkpoints in Colombo following intelligence
reports that rebels of the Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam (LTTE)
were targeting 17 strategic locations in the capital city.
</P>
<P>
Police sources said here today that police forces, together
with the armed forces, have stepped up their search operations
both in the city proper and the suburbs to hound some 20 rebels
who reportedly have penetrated into the city for attacks.
</P>
<P>
The residence of President Chandrika Kumaratunga, the
parliament premises, the state television station, military and
police headquarters, as well as other important facilities are on
the rebel hit list, according to the sources.
</P>
<P>
Security around these institutions has been tightened, the
sources said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
