<HEADLINE> People's Daily Editorial on Creating New Economic Situation (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The editorial called on the Chinese people to have an all-round
and correct understanding of the current situation.
</P>
<P>
Only in this way can the people correctly understand and
implement all policy decisions adopted by the CPC Central
Committee on economic development, it said.
</P>
<P>
"We should maintain the policy of seeking progress on the basis
of steady development, which was put forward in accordance with
historical experience and the reality of China's economic
growth," it added.
</P>
<P>
In maintaining steady development, the editorial said, "We
shall continue to practice a tight monetary control policy, curb
inflation, strengthen agricultural development, prevent and solve
financial risks and do a good job in social security so as to
maintain a stable macro-economic and social environment."
</P>
<P>
Making progress means a breakthrough in the reforms of
state-owned enterprises, financial systems, economic structures
and in the solution of major social problems. Meanwhile, the
overall quality of the national economy and efficiency should be
improved substantially, it added.
</P>
<P>
On this major premise, the country will seek a relatively rapid
development. Stability and progress should complement and promote
each other. Stability is the basis while progress is the purpose,
the editorial said.
</P>
<P>
Balancing reform, development and stability, we should take
care of the daily life of ordinary people and solve their
difficulties, the editorial said.
</P>
<P>
Leading officials at all levels should carry forward the fine
work style of hard struggle, clean-and-honest government and
maintenance of close ties with the masses, it said. 
