<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Computerizes Grain Transactions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 12 (Xinhua) -- A trading system has been
hooked up nationwide to initiate electronic processing of China's
grain transactions.
</P>
<P>
The network was set up by the China Chamber of Grain
Transactions, China Grain Trading Corp. (CGTC) and Xinhua Guoxin
Science and Trade Co. Ltd.
</P>
<P>
China is now the world's largest grain producer and also the
biggest grain importer. "The country attached equal importance to
grain production and circulation, both vital factors to ensure the
country's economic growth," said Shen Siyi, general manager of
CGTC.
</P>
<P>
"The newly founded network thoroughly changed the traditional
grain transaction method, thus meeting the requirements of huge
grain transaction volumes in China," he said.
</P>
<P>
Already connected to the Internet, the system timely displays
in Chinese the ever-changing information on grain prices in both
domestic and international markets. Also found in the network's
database are China's grain policy and other market analyses
released by the Chinese State Grain Reserve Administration.
</P>
<P>
With the aid of the network, sellers can deal with buyers by
keying in data on prices and amounts in the standard contract
provided by the system.
</P>
<P>
Up to 300 major enterprises nationwide who are engaged in grain
production, storage, processing and trade have become registered
members of the network. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
