<HEADLINE> Canadian Banks Raise Mortgage Rates </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, December 11 (Xinhua) -- Canada's commercial banks
raised mortgage rates by as much as 0.35 percentage point Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The Royal Bank, the country's biggest, increased short-term and
long-term mortgage rates between a fifth and more than a third of a
percentage point.
</P>
<P>
It was quickly followed by other commercial banks. The new
rates will come into effect Friday.
</P>
<P>
The banks said they raised the mortgage rates as a result of an
increase in their cost of borrowing money on the bond market.
</P>
<P>
To Canadian consumers, the increased rates mean they will have
to pay more if they borrow to buy houses and big-ticket items.
</P>
