<HEADLINE> Brazil To Create Amazon Biotechnology Center </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, December 11 (Xinhua) -- Brazil will set up a
biotechnology center for the Amazon in Manaus, in the northwest of
the country, says Brazilian Vice President Marco Maciel.
</P>
<P>
The construction of the biotechnology center, which is expected
to cost five million U.S. dollars, will start in 1999 and last
five years, Maciel said.
</P>
<P>
He said the center will aim at promoting research of plants and
animals of the Amazon to obtain materials for the pharmaceutical
and cosmetics industries.
</P>
<P>
The Amazon was "a very important area" that would have an
outstanding role in the 21st century for the earth, he said.
</P>
<P>
Brazil has rich resources of plants and animals, especially in
its Amazonian zone, which has more than five million square
kilometers of the total seven million square kilometers (2.7
million square miles) Amazonian region. 
</P>
</TEXT>
