<HEADLINE> Manninen Wins Nordic Combined Event Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, December 11 (Xinhua) -- Hannu Manninen of Finland
won the World Cup Nordic sprint combined event in Steamboat
Spring, Colorado, on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The 19-year-old Manninen, who was eighth in 90-meter jumping at
Howelsen Hill, edged Austrian Mario Stecher and Norwegian Bjarte
Engen Vik by erasing a 45-second and and 17-second deficit to
claim the victory.
</P>
<P>
The third victory of his career lifted Manninen into the World
Cup points lead after three events with 375 points.
</P>
<P>
Former leader Stecher placed third, 16.1 seconds behind
Manninen, slipping to the standings at 350 points, while Vik, who
finished second just 1.4 seconds behind the winner in the combined
event, ranking second with 350 points.
</P>
<P>
The individual sprint event included one ski jump and a
7.5-kilometer cross-country ski race.  
</P>
