<HEADLINE> Chinese People Seek Safe Sex Products </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, December 12 (Xinhua) -- A chain of stores known as
"Adam" or "Eve", which market safe sex and provide consultations
related to practicing safe sex, have opened in a number of
Chinese cities.
</P>
<P>
Recent resports indicate that a dozen stores have opened in
Changsha, capital of central China's Hunan Province.
</P>
<P>
The owner of five chain stores in the city noted that business
has been somewhat slow due to the fact that many safe sex products
are too expensive for common citizens. Nonetheless, he expressed
great confidence in the potential for future profitability.
</P>
<P>
A recent survey shows that the vast majority of consumers of
sex care products are educated people and professionals, including
doctors, lawyers and engineers.
</P>
<P>
Sexual research associations have been established in a number
of areas, with sex care radio programs gaining great popularity
amongst listeners.
</P>
<P>
Medical experts point out that Chinese people needs to learn
more about safe sex, and that large numbers of people will benefit
greatly from sex care products developed with the help of modern
technology. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
