<HEADLINE> Fires Cause Huge Losses to Oil Firms in Venezuela </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CARACAS, December 11 (Xinhua) -- Two fires occurred on Thursday
night in Venezuelan oil refineries, causing huge economic losses
and forcing the local authorities to declare one of the zones area
of emergency.
</P>
<P>
No casualties were reported, the Fire Department said.
</P>
<P>
The first fire started in an oil refinery in Guacara, state of
Carabobo.
</P>
<P>
The fire was so big that the local authorities had to declare
the area a zone of emergency.
</P>
<P>
Experts with the Service of Intelligence and Prevention
Direction the Technical Judicial Police have begun investigations
to establish the cause of the fire.
</P>
<P>
While firefighters were fighting the fire in the refinery,
another fire occurred in the Cardon refinery in the state of
Falco, where a boiler blew up.
</P>
<P>
The government of the Falcon state estimated the economic
losses at millions of U.S. dollars. 
</P>
