<HEADLINE> World Bank Approves Loan to Combat El Nino in El Ecuador </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, December 11 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank today
approved a 60 million U.S. dollar loan to Ecuador to help prevent
and repair damage to services and infrastructure in areas affected
by the El Nino phenomenon.
</P>
<P>
The El Nino Emergency Recovery Project will finance works,
goods, and services for the implementation of subprojects to
protect and rehabilitate public infrastructure associated with
port, airports, roads and bridges as well as flood protection and
drainage, water supply and sewerage, municipal service,
irrigation, electricity supply and distribution, health and
sanitation, education and resettlement.
</P>
<P>
The Ecuador government set up an Emergency Program totaling
some 230 million dollars to combat consequences of El Nino. With
the 60 million dollar loan approved today and an additional 20
million dollars from the World Bank's portfolio of existing
projects, the World bank will concentrate on financing damaged
infrastructure. The government of Ecuador will contribute 20
million dollars to the program. 
</P>
</TEXT>
