<HEADLINE> Denktash Should Be Pressured to Face Reality: </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, December 11 (Xinhua) -- Greek Foreign Undersecretary
Yiannos Kranidiotis today urged Turkish Cypriot political
organizations to pressure north Cyprus leader Rauf Denktash to
face reality in order to help settle the Cyprus problem.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a conference entitled "The Cyprus Problem: Prospect
of Solution" in Athens today, Kranidiotis said that Denktash was
seeking to perpetuate the Cyprus problem by maintaining
intransigence in talks with Cypriot President Glafcos Clerides.
</P>
<P>
He accused Denktash of using the Turkish Cypriot community as a
"vehicle" to further Turkish designs, particularly its efforts to
come closer to Europe.
</P>
<P>
Kranidiotis appealed to Turkish Cypriot political groups to
exert pressure on Denktash in order to force him to "tone down"
his intransigence and "see reality."
</P>
<P>
As for the prospect of Cyprus' accession to the European Union,
he stressed that this provides the greatest ever opportunity since
1974 for the settlement of the political problem.
</P>
<P>
He said that the Turkish Cypriot community could participate in
the accession negotiations only as part of the Cyprus Republic
delegation.
</P>
<P>
Cyprus has been divided since 1974 when Turkish troops invaded
and occupied the northern third of the island after a pro-Athens
coup.
</P>
<P>
Leaders of the two communities of the island have since this
year held three rounds of direct talks in order to resolve their
differences, but no real progress has been made so far. 
</P>
</TEXT>
