<HEADLINE> (Updated) IDB Approves Financing to Assist </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, December 11 (Xinhua) -- The Inter-American
Development Bank (IDB) today announced the approval of a 40
million U.S. dollar soft loan to help Nicaragua increase the
productivity of small and medium-sized farms.
</P>
<P>
The resources will provide farmers with training and
technological transfer as well as instruction in the better use of
renewable natural resources.
</P>
<P>
