<HEADLINE> IDB Approves Financing to Assist Agriculture in Nicaragua </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, December 11 (Xinhua) -- The Inter-American
Development Bank (IDB) today announced the approval of a 40
million U.S. dollar soft loan to help Nicaragua increase the
productivity of small and medium-sized farms.
</P>
<P>
The resources will provide farmers with training and
technological transfer as well as instruction in the better use of
renewable natural resources.
</P>
<P>
Productive infrastructure will be rehabilitated and enhanced,
and access to markets by small producers will be improved.
</P>
<P>
The IDB loan from the Fund for Special Operations is for a
40-year term, with a 10-year grace period, at an annual interest
rate of 1 percent during the grace period and 2 percent
thereafter. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
